I don't like it at all. It is one of those things that you hear but can't do anything about. The people that use that slur, usually also use words that would get a white person an ... whooping. It annoys the heck out of me. I'm sorry but I think people should get in as much trouble as white people who use other terms.

 They do here. But, that's a whole different can of worms. Those that use racial slurs can taunt, but only to a certain point, depending on the one being insulted. Using the law, and having a level head, one can stop it from that individual, but there&#8217;s always another waiting in the wings.
 I am at the point now that when someone racially insults me, I embarrass them by asking them what it means (which I know for the most part &#8211; hate and disgust). 
 &#8220;Is that directed towards me or my kind?&#8221;
 &#8220;Yea, (insert slur here).&#8221;
 &#8220;Which one? Because I don&#8217;t know you, do I?&#8221;
 &#8220;(insert vulgar language and slurs)!&#8221;
 &#8220;If you don&#8217;t know me then you have no reason to speak to me. If you have anything other than words, then do it.&#8221;
 If he or she puts a hand on me, I then proceed to do all I have been taught to do to defend myself. That is all within the law.
 It will stop that altercation, but like I said, there&#8217;s another waiting to happen.

 So, unless you&#8217;re willing to do that, then I would suggest to take the insult and walk away.

 Years ago I was told to &#8220;let it go.&#8221; But, that just fuels the flame&#8230;and I learned that the hard way. These racists are like hyenas, they love to pick out and attack the weak.

 I won&#8217;t tolerate it.
